487.  If you ask me which is the real hereditary sin of human nature,
do you imagine I shall answer pride? or luxury? or ambition? or egotism? no;
I shall say indolence--who conquers indolence will conquer all the rest.

626.  Let me repeat it--He only is great who has the habits of greatness;
